## 4. Stakeholder Analysis
- Stakeholder Group
- Impact Severity: Low/Medium/High

## 5. Harm Scenarios
- Scenario: e.g., Bias in hiring, privacy breach
- Likelihood (1–5)
- Impact (1–5)
- Risk Score = Likelihood × Impact

## 6. Data Risk Assessment
- Data Types: Personal, Sensitive, Behavioral, External
- Data Quality: completeness, noise, proxy variables
- Data Rights: consent, retention, sharing

## 7. Technical Assessment
- Fairness Risks: protected attributes, subgroup balance
- Explainability: SHAP/LIME/Interpretability
- Safety & Security: adversarial attacks, prompt injection (if LLM), model extraction

## 8. Mitigation Plan
- Risk Description
- Control Applied
- Owner
- Status
- Residual Risk

## 9. Deployment & Monitoring Requirements
- Metrics: Accuracy, Drift, Fairness, Robustness, Latency
- Alert Thresholds: PSI >0.2, DI <0.8, TPR/FPR gap >10%
- Monitoring Frequency

## 10. Approval & Sign-Off
- Model Owner:
- Compliance / Legal:
- Security Lead:
- AI Governance Council:
